# Frontend Standards

- Use feature-based foldering and keep screens thin; move business logic to hooks/services.
- Keep components focused: one responsibility, typed props, and predictable rendering.
- Prefer local-first UX: read from local state/DB first, then sync in background.
- Avoid inline complex logic in JSX; extract helpers for readability and testing.
- Handle loading, empty, and error states explicitly on every user-facing screen.

# State and Data

- Use centralized stores only for shared state; keep ephemeral UI state local.
- Do not mutate state directly; use immutable updates.
- Use stable keys and memoization for long lists and score/task cards.
- Protect sensitive user data in client logs; never log full phone numbers or tokens.

# Accessibility and UX

- Keep touch targets and contrast mobile-friendly by default.
- Ensure critical flows (SOS, guide access) remain discoverable in 1-2 taps.
